# UI Components & React Patterns

## Use project wrappers, not React Native primitives

Prefer components from `@/components/` over native equivalents:

| Native | Use instead |
|--------|-------------|
| `Text` | `AppText` (or `AnimatedAppText` when animating) |
| `TextInput` | `TextInput` from `@/components/TextInput` |
| `TouchableOpacity` / pressables for actions | `Button` from `@/components/Button` |
| Layout helpers | `PageContainer`, `Card`, `FormWrapper`, etc. |

If no wrapper exists for a native component, **ask whether one should be created** before using the native component directly.

```tsx
// ❌ BAD
import { Text, TextInput, TouchableOpacity } from 'react-native';

<Text style={{ fontSize: 16 }}>Hello</Text>
<TouchableOpacity onPress={() => router.push('/login')}>
  <Text>Go</Text>
</TouchableOpacity>

// ✅ GOOD
import { AppText } from '@/components/AppText';
import { Button } from '@/components/Button';
import { TextInput } from '@/components/TextInput';

<AppText variant="body">Hello</AppText>
<Button label="Go" onPress={handleGo} />
```

## Do not restyle buttons or inputs

`Button`, `TextInput`, and related wrappers share a consistent design system. Use their built-in props (`type`, `variant`, `label`, etc.) — do not override with custom `style` for colors, padding, borders, or typography unless explicitly requested.

## Prefer named handlers over inline functions

Extract event handlers as named functions (typically `handle*` / `on*`) instead of inline arrow functions in JSX.

```tsx
// ❌ BAD
<Button label="Save" onPress={() => save(data)} />
<TextInput onChangeText={(v) => setName(v)} />

// ✅ GOOD
const handleSave = useCallback(() => {
  save(data);
}, [data, save]);

const handleNameChange = (value: string) => {
  setName(value);
};

<Button label="Save" onPress={handleSave} />
<TextInput onChangeText={handleNameChange} />
```

Use `useCallback` when the handler is passed to memoized children or appears in effect dependency arrays.

## Extract smaller components

When a screen or component grows complex (repeated JSX, distinct UI sections, or nested logic), extract focused subcomponents into the same file or a colocated file under `components/`.
